curam.util.message
Class CatEntry

java.lang.Object
  curam.util.message.CatEntry
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public final class CatEntry
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable

Curam Message Catalog Entry. A catalog entry corresponds to an application message, and can be used to construct an instance of AppException. Catalog entries are not normally created by user code. Instead, they are created by generated Curam code, based on definitions in Curam application message ".xml" files.

See Also:
MessageCatalog, Serialized Form
